n%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216e6da93-72ab-4dbe-b8c1-3356449ce557%5C%22%3EMake%20sure%20there%20is%20enough%20seating%20for%20all%20guests%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224269%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20dining%20table%20set%20with%20Christmas%20decorations%20in%20front%20of%20a%20tree%20and%20wreath.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6760797627808b3289cd647c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223202%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUse%20your%20head%20count%20to%20ensure%20everyone%20has%20a%20place%20to%20sit.%3Cp%3ERawpixel.com%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20seating%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20double%20check%20your%20head%20count%20and%20ensure%20everyone%20has%20a%20place%20to%20sit.%20Gottsman%20said%20this%20should%20also%20be%20done%20for%20more%20casual%20events%20like%20cocktail%20or%20dinner%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20have%20enough%20seating%20for%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Gottsman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d1ac3e9a-117a-4206-9ab4-108f7e7ee3b9%5C%22%3EAvoid%20creating%20a%20chaotic%20environment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEtiquette%20and%20hosting%20expert%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.carlashellis.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECarla%20Shellis%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20another%20common%20mistake%20hosts%20make%20is%20not%20considering%20how%20they%20want%20their%20event%20or%20home%20to%20feel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20yelling%20and%20scrambling%20to%20get%20things%20done%20at%20the%20last%20second%2C%20the%20host%20can%20unintentionally%20leave%20the%20space%20feeling%20more%20chaotic%20than%20welcoming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGottsman%20shared%20similar%20thoughts%2C%20telling%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20doorbell%20rings%20with%20your%20first%20guest%2C%20you%20should%20not%20still%20be%20in%20your%20hair%20rollers%2C%20or%20lighting%20candles%2C%20or%20racing%20around%20talking%20about%20how%20busy%20you%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20combat%20a%20chaotic%20situation%2C%20Shellis%20likes%20to%20play%20music%2C%20light%20candles%2C%20and%20clean%20the%20space%20before%20her%20guests%20arrive.%20She%20also%20gives%20herself%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20get%20everything%20done%20so%20she%20doesn't%20have%20to%20rush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22473487be-8eb9-443e-a610-bc29c1c47ee6%5C%22%3EBe%20cautious%20when%20serving%20alcohol%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20people%20toasting%20cheers%20with%20Champagne%20flutes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67535b738fbb2783ed3063e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224128%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlcohol%20can%20sometimes%20do%20more%20harm%20than%20good%20at%20a%20party.%3Cp%3Ewilpunt%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShellis%20told%20BI%20that%20serving%20too%20much%20alcohol%20is%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20create%20unnecessary%20issues%20at%20a%20party.%20That's%20why%20it's%20important%20to%20ensure%20everyone%20is%20enjoying%20themselves%20in%20moderation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Shellis%20said%20when%20people%20ask%20her%20if%20she%20has%20any%20more%20wine%2C%20she'll%20say%20no%20and%20redirect%20them%20by%20offering%20other%20beverages%20like%20iced%20tea%20or%20soda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%2030%20years%2C%20I've%20been%20hosting%20parties%2C%20and%20I'm%20going%20to%20tell%20you%20there's%20nothing%20that%20will%20kill%20a%20beautiful%20environment%20quicker%20than%20somebody%20that's%20hammered%20and%20acting%20foolish%2C%26quot%3B%20Shellis%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-to-avoid-when-hosting-for-holidays-etiquette-mistakes-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734783242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%2